[497.898681, "o", "\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[497.935938, "o", "\u001b[?1049h\u001b[22;0;0t\u001b[?1h\u001b=\r"]
[497.947562, "o", "\u001b[4mCRYPTSETUP\u001b[24m(8)                 Maintenance Commands                 \u001b[4mCRYPTSETUP\u001b[24m(8)\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mNAME\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       cryptsetup - manage plain dm-crypt, LUKS, and other encrypted volumes\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mSYNOPSIS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mcryptsetup <action> [<options>] <action args>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mDESCRIPTION\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       cryptsetup is used to conveniently setup dm-crypt managed device-mapper\u001b[m\r\n       mappings. These include plain dm-crypt volumes and LUKS volumes. The\u001b[m\r\n       difference is that LUKS uses a metadata header and can hence offer more\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page cryptsetup(8) line 1 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[498.665377, "o", "\r\u001b[K       features than plain dm-crypt. On the other hand, the header is visible\u001b[m\r\n       and vulnerable to damage.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       In addition, cryptsetup provides limited support for the use of loop-AES\u001b[m\r\n       volumes, TrueCrypt, VeraCrypt, BitLocker and FileVault2 compatible\u001b[m\r\n       volumes, and for hardware-based encryption on OPAL capable drives.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       For more information about specific cryptsetup action see\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mcryptsetup-<action>\u001b[22m(8), where \u001b[1m<action> \u001b[22mis the name of the cryptsetup\u001b[m\r\n       action.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mBASIC ACTIONS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page cryptsetup(8) line 13 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[498.975503, "o", "\r\u001b[K       The following are valid actions for all supported device types.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mOPEN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mopen <device> <name> --type <device_type>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Opens (creates a mapping with) <name> backed by device <device>.\u001b[m\r\n       See \u001b[1mcryptsetup-open\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mCLOSE\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mclose <name>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Removes the existing mapping <name> and wipes the key from kernel memory.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page cryptsetup(8) line 25 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[499.210894, "o", "\r\u001b[K       See \u001b[1mcryptsetup-close\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mSTATUS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mstatus <name>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Reports the status for the mapping <name>.\u001b[m\r\n       See \u001b[1mcryptsetup-status\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mRESIZE\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mresize <name>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Resizes an active mapping <name>.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page cryptsetup(8) line 37 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[500.304601, "o", "\r\u001b[K       See \u001b[1mcryptsetup-resize\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mREFRESH\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mrefresh <name>\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Refreshes parameters of active mapping <name>.\u001b[m\r\n       See \u001b[1mcryptsetup-refresh\u001b[22m(8).\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n   \u001b[1mREENCRYPT\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mreencrypt <device> or --active-name <name> [<new_name>]\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       Run LUKS device reencryption.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page cryptsetup(8) line 49 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[500.837216, "o", "\r\u001b[K\u001b[?1l\u001b>\u001b[?1049l\u001b[23;0;0t"]
